data.title: Visits by Foreign Leaders
data.text: Queen Wilhelmina In U.S. June 24–August 11. Vacationed in Lee (Massachusetts); visited New York City, Boston, and Albany (New York). August 5–7, 1942 Premier Drees Informal visit. In U.S. January 12–24, visiting New York City, Bridgeport (Connecticut) and Pittsburgh (Pennsylvania). January 20–23, 1952 Queen Juliana Addressed U.S. Congress April 3. Afterwards visited Philadelphia (Pennsylvania), New York City, Knoxville (Tennessee), Detroit, Grand Rapids, Holland, and Ann Arbor, (Michigan), San Francisco, and Los Angeles. Departed U.S. April 22. April 2–5, 1952 Prime Minister Petrus J. S. de Jong Official visit. In U.S. May 26–29; visited Williamsburg, Annapolis, and New York City. May 27–29, 1969 Prime Minister Barend Willem Biesheuvel Private visit. January 26, 1972 Prime Minister Johannes Marten den Uyl Private visit. First visit to the U.S. at invitation of the President. May 13–15, 1975 Prime Minister Andreas A. M. van Agt Attended North Atlantic Alliance Summit conference. May 30–31, 1978 Prime Minister Andreas A. M. van Agt Private visit. December 7, 1979 Prime Minister Andreas A. M. van Agt Official working visit. Met with Vice President Bush. March 30–April 1, 1981 Queen Beatrix State visit. Addressed Joint Session of U.S. Congress April 2l; visited Philadelphia and New York City. Departed U.S. April 24. April 18–22, 1982 Prime Minister Rudolphus F. M. (Ruud) Lubbers Official working visit. March 14–16, 1983 Prime Minister Rudolphus F. M. (Ruud) Lubbers Private visit. Met with President Reagan January 19. January 19–20, 1984 Prime Minister Rudolphus F. M. (Ruud) Lubbers Met with President Bush during a private visit. May 9, 1989 Prime Minister Rudolphus F. M. (Ruud) Lubbers Official working visit. January 4–5, 1994 Prime Minister Willem (Wim) Kok Official working visit. February 26–28, 1995 Queen Beatrix Met with President Clinton during a private visit. November 7–10, 1995 Prime Minister Ruud Lubbers Official working visit. January 4, 1999 Prime Minister Wim Kok Attended NATO’s 50th Anniversary Summit. April 23–25, 1999 Prime Minister Willem Kok Official working visit. September 27–28, 2000 Prime Minister Jan Peter Balkenende Working visit. September 3, 2003 Prime Minister Jan Balkenende Working visit. March 15–16, 2004 Prime Minister Jan Peter Balkenende Working visit. June 5–8, 2008 Prime Minister Jan Peter Balkenende Attended the G-20 Economic Summit Meeting. November 14–15, 2008 Prime Minister Jan Peter Balkenende Working Visit. July 14, 2009 Prime Minister Jan Peter Balkenende Attended the G-20 Economic Summit in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. September 24–25, 2009 Prime Minister Jan Peter Balkenende Attended the Nuclear Security Summit. April 12–13, 2010 Prime Minister Mark Rutte Working visit. November 28–29, 2011 Prime Minister Mark Rutte Attended the NATO Summit Meeting in Chicago, IL. May 20–21, 2012 King Willem-Alexander Official Working Visit. June 1, 2015
